WEBVTT

00:03.580 --> 00:04.830
Previously on "How to Get Away
With Murder"...

00:04.830 --> 00:06.210
We're gonna need you to do
a psychiatric evaluation.

00:06.210 --> 00:09.170
I just remember
I wanted a slice of cake.

00:09.170 --> 00:11.330
We get to argue
our insanity defense.

00:11.330 --> 00:12.880
Just answer the question!

00:12.880 --> 00:14.250
Why me?!
You know what?!

00:14.250 --> 00:15.670
I'm trying to change
the damn world here!

00:15.670 --> 00:17.080
Literally!

00:17.080 --> 00:19.120
Mr. Maddox,
you're now my second chair.

00:19.120 --> 00:21.420
Nate: It's her kid, Annalise.
Her kid who was a product
of rape.

00:21.420 --> 00:23.290
Where's her sister live?
Why do you care?

00:23.290 --> 00:25.250
So we can find out
what happened.

00:25.250 --> 00:26.710
Annalise:
It said your baby's alive.

00:26.710 --> 00:28.540
Please tell me
you don't believe that.

00:28.540 --> 00:29.580
I do.

00:29.580 --> 00:31.500
Emcee:
Oliver to the dance floor!

00:31.500 --> 00:32.830
Michaela: Let's all call him.
He has to be close.

00:32.830 --> 00:35.670
[ Cellphone ringing ]

00:35.670 --> 00:37.290
Nate: Leave a message.

00:37.290 --> 00:38.330
Are you still here?

00:38.330 --> 00:40.580
[ Sobbing ]

00:42.790 --> 00:52.790
♪♪

00:52.790 --> 00:54.580
♪♪

00:54.580 --> 00:55.620
[ Door closes ]

00:55.620 --> 00:59.540
♪♪

00:59.540 --> 01:06.620
♪♪

01:06.620 --> 01:09.960
We're gonna do a different type
of case review today.

01:09.960 --> 01:11.880
We're gonna call it an autopsy.

01:11.880 --> 01:13.330
So let's cut open the body

01:13.330 --> 01:15.420
and see where we went wrong
during the trial.

01:15.420 --> 01:17.750
Sorry...

01:17.750 --> 01:19.210
where I went wrong.

01:22.040 --> 01:23.790
[ Chalk scraping ]
I needed to prove

01:23.790 --> 01:28.170
that my client was insane

01:28.170 --> 01:31.210
at the time that he murdered
Gerald Reinhoff.

01:31.210 --> 01:33.460
So, what was my first mistake?

01:33.460 --> 01:37.120
♪♪

01:37.120 --> 01:38.120
Really?

01:38.120 --> 01:39.580
None of you thought

01:39.580 --> 01:41.540
that I made one mistake
during this trial?

01:41.540 --> 01:44.500
You screwed up with your
very first decision.

01:44.500 --> 01:48.540
You mean replacing you
as second chair with Mr. Maddox?

01:48.540 --> 01:51.460
I guess I'm talking about
your second decision, then.

01:51.460 --> 01:54.120
We have till noon tomorrow
to tell the judge

01:54.120 --> 01:57.960
if we're waiving our right to
a jury at Senior's trial.

01:57.960 --> 01:59.210
So let's hash it out --

01:59.210 --> 02:01.210
who votes jury,
who votes judge?

02:01.210 --> 02:03.620
You always go with a judge
on an insanity defense.

02:03.620 --> 02:05.710
When have you ever known me
to do what's expected?

02:05.710 --> 02:07.790
Okay, but if you start throwing
terms like "volitional act"

02:07.790 --> 02:10.000
and "defect of reason" at a
jury, you've already lost them.

02:10.000 --> 02:11.580
Yeah, but this case
is about emotion,

02:11.580 --> 02:13.460
making people feel
what Nate Senior felt

02:13.460 --> 02:15.460
when he was losing his mind
locked away in that cell.

02:15.460 --> 02:17.920
What is the biggest pitfall
of Mr. Maddox's strategy?
It's nice, right?

02:17.920 --> 02:19.620
Rhonda: One, think about the
emotion the jury will feel...
For a bar --

02:19.620 --> 02:21.580
Well, it's cheap, and it's
available on the 15th.

02:21.580 --> 02:23.080
We should book it.
My mom has a church retreat

02:23.080 --> 02:24.170
every year
around the holidays.

02:24.170 --> 02:26.330
Annalise: Do you think
he'll be on our side...
I have to make sure
she's free.

02:26.330 --> 02:27.620
...or the prosecution's?
For her son's wedding?

02:27.620 --> 02:29.540
Do you agree, Mr. Walsh?

02:29.540 --> 02:31.120
I'm sorry,
what was the question?

02:31.120 --> 02:34.210
Do you think Judge Coughlin will
be biased against our case?

02:34.210 --> 02:37.830
I think whatever
Gabriel thinks.

02:42.670 --> 02:44.380
I agree with Mr. Maddox, too.

02:44.380 --> 02:46.460
So, I believe
our best bet is a...

02:46.460 --> 02:47.960
...jury trial.

02:47.960 --> 02:49.540
Now, it's a big swing,

02:49.540 --> 02:51.620
but your name is on
the Supreme Court win,

02:51.620 --> 02:53.500
not to mention
you're a likable guy.

02:53.500 --> 02:54.620
When he wants to be.

02:54.620 --> 02:56.210
[ Chuckles ]

02:56.210 --> 02:58.710
Judges been messing
with me my whole life.

02:58.710 --> 03:02.290
I finally get to take the stand
in front of my peers.

03:02.290 --> 03:03.790
Well, that's not
what we're saying.

03:03.790 --> 03:05.120
Our case is strong,

03:05.120 --> 03:07.670
and we probably won't even need
to put you on the stand.

03:09.290 --> 03:11.080
Nate: You don't put your
sane clients on the stand.

03:11.080 --> 03:12.920
Why make it seem like
that was a possibility?

03:12.920 --> 03:14.830
I tell my clients what they
want to hear, and then I win,

03:14.830 --> 03:16.000
and they forget
all about it.

03:16.000 --> 03:17.250
I'm late.
How is she?

03:18.500 --> 03:19.920
How do you think?

03:22.620 --> 03:23.790
[ Keys jingling ]

03:26.000 --> 03:27.000
Frank.

03:27.000 --> 03:28.120
[ Door closes ]

03:28.120 --> 03:30.330
[ Sighs ]
You had one job!

03:32.000 --> 03:34.120
Bonnie?
[ Knock on door ]

03:34.120 --> 03:36.210
[ Door creaks ]

03:36.210 --> 03:37.420
You asleep?

03:37.420 --> 03:39.330
♪♪

03:39.330 --> 03:49.620
♪♪

03:49.620 --> 03:51.540
I never wanted anything bad
to come of this.

03:53.580 --> 03:54.460
I mean it.

03:57.290 --> 03:59.380
I thought
I was doing this for you.

03:59.380 --> 04:02.620
Then why tell Annalise
before me?

04:02.620 --> 04:04.580
Annalise knows you the best.

04:04.580 --> 04:06.290
I thought maybe she could
help me figure out that --

04:06.290 --> 04:08.170
That I kidnapped
my own baby?

04:10.170 --> 04:11.620
Or that I killed him?

04:11.620 --> 04:13.920
All I was trying to do
is help you.

04:13.920 --> 04:17.000
[ Breathes deeply ]

04:17.000 --> 04:19.080
You ripped open
the part of my life

04:19.080 --> 04:21.750
that I killed myself
to get past.

04:23.210 --> 04:24.880
And I got past it.

04:27.330 --> 04:30.580
I was good.

04:30.580 --> 04:31.920
But now...

04:35.210 --> 04:36.710
What can I do?

04:37.750 --> 04:41.920
That's the problem.

04:41.920 --> 04:46.040
You did what you did
and now I'm left with it.

04:49.250 --> 04:51.960
It's always me
that's left with it.

04:51.960 --> 04:54.080
All right, hold up.

04:54.080 --> 04:55.000
Bonnie.

04:59.040 --> 05:00.380
[ Door closes ]

05:04.620 --> 05:06.290
She's probably
at her boyfriend's.

05:06.290 --> 05:08.290
Or she drove off a bridge.

05:09.830 --> 05:12.620
Or went to Julie's
and drove her off a bridge.

05:12.620 --> 05:14.750
[ Door unlocks ]

05:14.750 --> 05:16.170
[ Keys jingling ]

05:16.170 --> 05:17.710
Where the hell'd you go?

05:19.540 --> 05:20.380
Nate's.

05:21.880 --> 05:23.420
I'm going to sleep.

05:23.420 --> 05:24.920
Bonnie...

05:26.250 --> 05:28.380
I'm not gonna do
anything stupid.

05:31.500 --> 05:35.250
[ Footsteps leaving ]

05:35.250 --> 05:37.500
I'll hide all
the razor blades.

05:37.500 --> 05:39.790
[ Cellphone ringing ]

05:39.790 --> 05:41.000
Nate?

05:41.000 --> 05:43.330
No, my 2L.
Calling this late?

05:43.330 --> 05:45.540
Oh, well, he's my new favorite,
so he's allowed.

05:45.540 --> 05:47.120
What?
Prosecution
just sent over

05:47.120 --> 05:48.460
their new witness list.

05:48.460 --> 05:51.080
They added a new name.
Who?

05:51.080 --> 05:52.460
Connor: You also failed
to properly prepare

05:52.460 --> 05:54.210
for the prosecution's
first witness.

05:54.210 --> 05:55.170
You mean
their hostile witness?

05:55.170 --> 05:56.960
I mean your client's son --

05:56.960 --> 05:59.170
Nate Lahey, Junior.

05:59.170 --> 06:01.710
You knew about his complicated
history with his father,

06:01.710 --> 06:03.750
and yet you failed to grill him
before he took the stand.

06:03.750 --> 06:05.460
She did. I was there.

06:05.460 --> 06:07.920
Okay, well, then
I guess she did a bad job

06:07.920 --> 06:10.210
considering the bomb
the prosecution dropped.

06:10.210 --> 06:11.420
How could she have
seen that coming?

06:11.420 --> 06:13.000
I don't know, second chair.

06:13.000 --> 06:15.000
I guess that was your job.

06:15.000 --> 06:17.790
Cox: Mr. Lahey, how old
were you when you discovered

06:17.790 --> 06:19.790
your father sold drugs?

06:19.790 --> 06:21.750
I don't recall.
But you're not
disputing the fact

06:21.750 --> 06:23.880
that you were aware that your
father was a drug dealer

06:23.880 --> 06:26.540
of marijuana and crack?

06:26.540 --> 06:28.330
My pops dropped out of school
when he was 16

06:28.330 --> 06:30.380
to box professionally.

06:30.380 --> 06:32.790
When that didn't
pay the bills,

06:32.790 --> 06:34.330
there weren't a lot
of other options.

06:34.330 --> 06:36.210
When you father was living
at home with you,

06:36.210 --> 06:38.170
what was his mood
around the house?

06:38.170 --> 06:39.710
Was he angry?
Objection!

06:39.710 --> 06:41.620
You can't testify to someone
else's state of mind.

06:41.620 --> 06:43.210
Sustained.

06:43.210 --> 06:44.500
Cox:
He was a boxer, though.

06:44.500 --> 06:46.040
Must've knocked you
around a bit, yeah?

06:46.040 --> 06:48.290
He was a boxer
in the ring only.

06:48.290 --> 06:49.750
Never took his work
home with him.

06:49.750 --> 06:52.830
So you're saying you felt
your home was a safe place?

06:52.830 --> 06:54.380
Yes.

06:54.380 --> 06:56.710
Your Honor, I'd like to
introduce as evidence

06:56.710 --> 06:58.500
a letter written
by the witness --
Objection!

06:58.500 --> 07:00.710
This letter wasn't in
any of the discovery.

07:00.710 --> 07:02.920
The letter has only just now
become relevant, Your Honor.

07:02.920 --> 07:04.500
Judge Coughlin: All right,
both of you up to the bench.

07:04.500 --> 07:06.960
Now.

07:06.960 --> 07:08.670
They buried that letter
on purpose.

07:08.670 --> 07:09.830
There was nothing
she could've done.

07:09.830 --> 07:11.540
She could've gotten it
thrown out as hearsay.

07:11.540 --> 07:13.250
Her only option was to
challenge its relevance.

07:13.250 --> 07:14.750
How is this letter
relevant at all?

07:14.750 --> 07:16.210
It's written by
the defendant's son.

07:16.210 --> 07:17.710
A year before the murder
in question.

07:17.710 --> 07:20.000
This letter is permissible
to show lack of accident,

07:20.000 --> 07:21.080
perhaps even motive.

07:21.080 --> 07:22.500
It is character evidence --

07:22.500 --> 07:24.080
It's character assassination,
Judge.

07:24.080 --> 07:25.540
The whole point of this
exercise is to figure out

07:25.540 --> 07:27.380
where you and Professor Keating
went wrong.

07:27.380 --> 07:28.750
Why are you getting
so defensive?

07:28.750 --> 07:30.000
'Cause that's what
a real lawyer does --

07:30.000 --> 07:31.000
defends their client.

07:31.000 --> 07:32.960
You're not a real lawyer.

07:32.960 --> 07:34.830
You're just her
little mini-me.

07:34.830 --> 07:37.250
Sit down --
No. You hid in the back
of that courtroom

07:37.250 --> 07:38.460
like a baby
the entire case,

07:38.460 --> 07:39.790
and now you have
something to say?

07:39.790 --> 07:41.790
And you sat shotgun
and let her drive this case

07:41.790 --> 07:42.670
straight off a cliff.

07:42.670 --> 07:44.460
I said sit down!

07:44.460 --> 07:47.790
This is a law school...

07:47.790 --> 07:50.080
not a daycare.

07:50.080 --> 07:51.580
The judge ruled against us.

07:51.580 --> 07:53.460
So, what could
I have done next?

07:53.460 --> 07:56.750
Cox: Mr. Lahey, you testified
that you felt safe at home,

07:56.750 --> 07:59.580
but you wrote this letter to
your father's Parole Board

07:59.580 --> 08:01.210
when you were 14.

08:01.210 --> 08:03.040
Would you please read
the second paragraph?

08:04.580 --> 08:06.880
"I was told to write
this letter

08:06.880 --> 08:09.250
to convince you to
let my pops come home.

08:09.250 --> 08:11.210
But I don't want him
to come home.

08:11.210 --> 08:13.000
My moms and I are
doing good without him,

08:13.000 --> 08:14.710
but that will all change

08:14.710 --> 08:17.290
if you believe his lies
and let him out."

08:19.670 --> 08:24.750
"Please just know
I feel safer...

08:24.750 --> 08:26.830
with him behind bars."

08:26.830 --> 08:28.330
[ Sighs ]

08:28.330 --> 08:29.170
Thank you.

08:31.170 --> 08:32.290
You did this on purpose,
didn't you?

08:32.290 --> 08:34.170
You heard what I said
on the stand.

08:34.170 --> 08:35.540
I-I don't remember
writing it.

08:35.540 --> 08:37.330
Yeah, well I remember everything
that happened after that.

08:37.330 --> 08:39.380
I was supposed to win
that parole hearing!

08:39.380 --> 08:40.750
We'll never know
if that letter

08:40.750 --> 08:42.040
was the reason you lost
the hearing --

08:42.040 --> 08:43.620
You want to know what happened
after that? Huh?

08:43.620 --> 08:45.080
I started picking fights
with everybody,

08:45.080 --> 08:46.540
disrespecting the guards.

08:46.540 --> 08:48.500
That's when they
put me in the SHU.

08:50.830 --> 08:52.380
All of this...

08:54.710 --> 08:56.920
Me losing my mind,

08:56.920 --> 08:59.500
me killing that man --

08:59.500 --> 09:05.210
all of this because of you
and that letter.

09:05.210 --> 09:07.120
You finished?

09:07.120 --> 09:09.120
'Cause we still
have a case to win.

09:09.120 --> 09:11.330
Keep him away from me.

09:11.330 --> 09:12.790
I don't want to see
his face again.

09:12.790 --> 09:15.380
You better want to,
because it's his face

09:15.380 --> 09:17.420
the jury needs to see
in that courtroom --

09:17.420 --> 09:19.380
someone who loves you.

09:19.380 --> 09:24.000
Otherwise you're the bastard
who turned on his own son.

09:24.000 --> 09:28.330
♪♪

09:35.210 --> 09:36.080
Sophie:
Professor Keating, my criticism

09:36.080 --> 09:37.290
isn't that you didn't get
the letter thrown out,

09:37.290 --> 09:38.670
but that you didn't go
at the witness hard enough

09:38.670 --> 09:39.880
during your cross.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.620
How is discrediting
the defendant's son,

09:41.620 --> 09:44.330
someone on our witness list,
helping to win over the jury?

09:44.330 --> 09:45.880
Desperate times call
for desperate measures.

09:45.880 --> 09:47.540
A good lawyer should
never be desperate.

09:47.540 --> 09:49.830
Professor Keating lost this
round because of one reason --

09:49.830 --> 09:51.750
she didn't see
the letter coming.

09:51.750 --> 09:52.830
Why didn't I see it coming?

09:54.210 --> 09:55.750
You were too close
to the witness.

09:58.500 --> 10:00.380
Connor: You know, this all
could've been avoided

10:00.380 --> 10:02.210
if you'd just done the research
and found that letter.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.460
Sounds like
your boyfriend's job.

10:03.460 --> 10:06.250
Uh, fiancé, and is anyone
really to blame here?

10:06.250 --> 10:07.580
Yeah, the guy
who wrote the letter.

10:07.580 --> 10:09.500
We all do stupid things
when we're 14.

10:09.500 --> 10:11.670
Pretty sure he wasn't 14
when he chose to become a cop.

10:11.670 --> 10:13.540
What does him being a cop
have to do with anything?

10:13.540 --> 10:15.170
What kind of guy turns
his back on his own people?

10:15.170 --> 10:17.540
Okay, none of this helps
our case right now.

10:17.540 --> 10:18.580
Exactly.

10:18.580 --> 10:20.170
I'm going to C&G
to prep for tomorrow.

10:21.540 --> 10:23.540
Are you trying to
get him to punch you?

10:23.540 --> 10:24.710
Where are you going?

10:24.710 --> 10:26.670
Oh, uh, he needs
my Antitrust outline.

10:26.670 --> 10:28.000
I'll see you guys
back at the house.

10:29.210 --> 10:30.830
Those two guys
friends again?

10:30.830 --> 10:33.290
Eh, they're probably
just boning.

10:33.290 --> 10:35.080
If we're gonna do this,
we need to be more discreet,

10:35.080 --> 10:36.500
and we need some
ground rules.

10:36.500 --> 10:38.080
Mm, ground rules kinda
take the fun

10:38.080 --> 10:39.750
out of
"Operation Slama Jama."

10:39.750 --> 10:41.250
Okay --

10:41.250 --> 10:42.920
Rule one,
no more calling it that.

10:42.920 --> 10:45.540
Two, no work talk.
Three, no relationship talk.

10:45.540 --> 10:48.080
Good, because that
is never happening again.

10:48.080 --> 10:49.290
[ Horn honks in distance ]

10:49.290 --> 10:50.710
Your place tonight?

10:50.710 --> 10:53.250
Think I can, uh,
squeeze you in.

10:53.250 --> 10:54.500
Great.

10:54.500 --> 10:56.420
Have you heard anything
about Bonnie?

10:56.420 --> 10:57.710
She hasn't been at work
in a few days.

10:57.710 --> 10:59.500
Are you interested
in her again?

10:59.500 --> 11:01.620
No, I'm worried about her
as a friend.

11:02.620 --> 11:04.330
Mm-hmm.

11:04.330 --> 11:06.500
I can be friends
with girls, Michaela!

11:06.500 --> 11:10.540
♪♪

11:10.540 --> 11:11.670
[ Knock on door ]

11:11.670 --> 11:13.920
♪♪

11:14.750 --> 11:15.750
[ Sighs ]

11:15.750 --> 11:16.790
Frank, buddy.

11:16.790 --> 11:18.330
How's it going?

11:18.330 --> 11:19.710
Good until now.

11:19.710 --> 11:21.040
[ Scoffs ]

11:21.040 --> 11:22.960
Okay, bro,
what the hell is going on?

11:22.960 --> 11:24.080
She's sick.

11:24.080 --> 11:26.420
Uh, yeah,
but what kind of sick?

11:26.420 --> 11:28.290
Because if it's serious,
her boss needs to know.

11:28.290 --> 11:30.920
So you came here
as her boss?

11:30.920 --> 11:33.540
She won't answer my calls,

11:33.540 --> 11:34.920
and if that's because
I freaked her out

11:34.920 --> 11:37.670
with that stupid HR form,
you tell her to forget it.

11:37.670 --> 11:39.080
I'll pass along
the message.

11:39.080 --> 11:41.420
Look, I-I want to be the one
to pass along the message.

11:41.420 --> 11:43.500
Sorry...

11:43.500 --> 11:45.040
bro.

11:45.040 --> 11:46.120
[ Door creaks lightly ]

11:47.540 --> 11:49.170
Frank: It's gotta
make you feel pretty good,

11:49.170 --> 11:52.120
having your beau so smitten
he's begging for your attention.

11:52.120 --> 11:58.580
♪♪

11:58.580 --> 12:02.330
I know you're telling yourself
you need to find out the truth.

12:04.380 --> 12:07.880
But just consider
the other option.

12:07.880 --> 12:09.170
You do nothing.

12:11.540 --> 12:13.250
'Cause you've been happy...

12:15.380 --> 12:17.960
...way more than
I've ever seen.

12:17.960 --> 12:21.670
But no one --
I mean no one, Bon,

12:21.670 --> 12:24.290
deserves to be happy
more than you.

12:24.290 --> 12:28.420
So, if you just want to pretend
you never found this out,

12:28.420 --> 12:32.960
leave the past in the past,
know I fully support that.

12:32.960 --> 12:41.750
♪♪

12:41.750 --> 12:44.080
Mm. [ Sniffles ]

12:44.080 --> 12:45.960
♪♪

12:45.960 --> 12:47.620
[ Door creaks lightly ]

12:47.620 --> 12:49.250
[ Door closes ]

12:49.250 --> 12:55.880
♪♪

12:55.880 --> 12:57.790
You know what I'd do
if I were you?

13:00.500 --> 13:03.380
I'd pour myself
a stiff drink.

13:03.380 --> 13:05.830
I'm good.

13:05.830 --> 13:08.620
At least we have
the psych expert on our side.

13:08.620 --> 13:09.960
I mean, that's all
we really need --

13:09.960 --> 13:11.500
I lied on the stand,
Annalise.

13:15.170 --> 13:17.210
I remember writing
the letter.

13:19.580 --> 13:21.750
You were just a boy.

13:21.750 --> 13:24.210
God knows what I said to
my mother at that age --
Just listen.

13:25.830 --> 13:29.960
First time I saw him in cuffs,
I was pissed at the cops.

13:32.330 --> 13:35.710
But by the second, the third,
the fourth...

13:39.250 --> 13:44.620
I began thinking he wasn't
the good guy, they were.

13:46.380 --> 13:48.210
So I decided to be
one of them.

13:53.250 --> 13:57.580
[ Breathes deeply ]

13:59.920 --> 14:03.080
So at least I wouldn't
end up like him.

14:03.080 --> 14:05.000
If you beat yourself up
over this,

14:05.000 --> 14:08.670
the same system that got in his
head is gonna get into yours.

14:08.670 --> 14:10.330
[ Breathes deeply ]

14:10.330 --> 14:12.000
What if all this
is for nothing?

14:12.000 --> 14:13.880
Do you think I would
drag our asses

14:13.880 --> 14:15.460
all the way to
the Supreme Court

14:15.460 --> 14:17.500
only to lose in Philly?
[ Chuckles ]

14:17.500 --> 14:18.710
We're gonna win.

14:19.920 --> 14:21.210
All right.
[ Chuckles ]

14:22.540 --> 14:25.080
Okay.

14:25.080 --> 14:26.170
All right.

14:26.170 --> 14:29.290
♪♪

14:33.960 --> 14:40.460
♪♪

14:40.460 --> 14:42.380
Michaela: As down
as we might all feel right now,

14:42.380 --> 14:43.880
I think it's important
that we focus on

14:43.880 --> 14:45.620
one of the wins
we had on this case.

14:45.620 --> 14:49.040
I believe your cross of
the prosecution's psych expert

14:49.040 --> 14:50.790
was an unqualified success.

14:50.790 --> 14:53.620
Does everyone agree that I won
the round against Dr. Charmagne?

14:53.620 --> 14:55.290
I think you won.
I just don't understand

14:55.290 --> 14:56.790
how you got that intel.

14:56.790 --> 14:58.500
Ms. Pratt, would you like
to answer that one?

14:58.500 --> 15:00.790
A good lawyer never reveals
their deep throat.

15:00.790 --> 15:02.380
[ Knock on door ]

15:02.380 --> 15:03.830
♪ She don't wanna duck me ♪
Asher!

15:03.830 --> 15:05.330
♪ She just wanna show me love ♪

15:05.330 --> 15:06.580
♪ She don't wanna cuff me ♪
Open up!

15:06.580 --> 15:08.620
♪ Mad 'cause I'm on now ♪

15:08.620 --> 15:10.170
♪ You can't leave me alone now ♪

15:10.170 --> 15:12.210
♪ Got my mama strong now ♪
What the hell?

15:12.210 --> 15:14.330
♪ Tryna reach the throne,
yeah, yeah, yeah ♪
I'm working on our
"Slama Jama" playlist!

15:14.330 --> 15:17.290
♪ See everybody want a handout ♪
Hope you brought
your backup panties!

15:17.290 --> 15:18.750
♪ I'm tryna get it ♪
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

15:18.750 --> 15:20.290
[ Music stops ]
This -- [ Scoffs ]

15:20.290 --> 15:23.210
I need your help
with our case.

15:23.210 --> 15:25.040
We said no work talk!
It's not about work.

15:25.040 --> 15:26.500
It's about Nate.

15:26.500 --> 15:28.120
The prosecution's putting
their psychologist

15:28.120 --> 15:31.580
on the stand tomorrow,
his name's Dr. Charmagne --
Yeah, Dr. Charming.

15:31.580 --> 15:33.620
He's the most handsome,
likable expert out there.

15:33.620 --> 15:35.210
We need to discredit him.

15:35.210 --> 15:37.790
The D.A.'s office uses him as
a psych expert all the time --

15:37.790 --> 15:39.580
You do realize you're still
in the doghouse with me --

15:39.580 --> 15:42.330
You think I'm a heartless bitch,
I understand why...

15:43.670 --> 15:46.710
...but your heart --
your heart is big and kind,

15:46.710 --> 15:48.960
and that's why
I fell for you --
Stop.

15:48.960 --> 15:50.750
Look, I have a good thing going
with the D.A., all right?

15:50.750 --> 15:52.960
I'm finally getting
my life back on track.

15:52.960 --> 15:54.120
And now you want me to
risk that all

15:54.120 --> 15:56.000
for you and --
and Annalise?

15:56.000 --> 15:59.710
Are --
Just take me and Annalise
out of the equation.

15:59.710 --> 16:02.500
If Nate was the one
coming to you right now,

16:02.500 --> 16:04.580
you'd do this for him.

16:04.580 --> 16:05.540
Right?

16:05.540 --> 16:07.210
♪♪

16:07.210 --> 16:08.540
[ Knock on door ]

16:10.540 --> 16:12.210
Oh, hell, no.

16:14.460 --> 16:16.620
None of you are supposed
to know where I live.
Yeah, they don't.

16:16.620 --> 16:18.330
But since I'm the brilliant
and resourceful student

16:18.330 --> 16:20.250
you mistakenly passed up
on your clinic --

16:20.250 --> 16:22.710
Someone in the D.A.'s office
gave you my address.

16:22.710 --> 16:26.080
A-And I have the info you need
to take down Dr. Charming.

16:27.500 --> 16:28.420
Dah!

16:28.420 --> 16:29.750
First, why don't
you tell me

16:29.750 --> 16:32.880
what's going on
with Bonnie?

16:32.880 --> 16:34.790
Nothing is going on.

16:34.790 --> 16:37.880
Tell me what is up
or no juicy intel for you.

16:37.880 --> 16:39.210
What do you think?

16:42.210 --> 16:43.420
What the hell is this?
Robert: Don't worry --

16:43.420 --> 16:45.330
Bonnie's childhood.
And that man...

16:45.330 --> 16:46.790
It's gonna be fun.
...is her father.

16:48.880 --> 16:50.250
Can I do anything?

16:50.250 --> 16:52.710
No, you can give
her some space.

16:52.710 --> 16:54.620
Don't tell the others,
especially Miller.

16:54.620 --> 16:57.080
Of course not.
Now pony up.

16:59.500 --> 17:03.420
According to the D.A.'s
database, Senior's case

17:03.420 --> 17:05.830
is the last time Dr. Charming
is allowed to testify.

17:05.830 --> 17:08.540
Why?
Why do you think?

17:08.540 --> 17:10.040
[In Cockney accent]
Hello, Governor.

17:11.080 --> 17:14.960
Dr. Charmagne, do you believe
that the defendant was insane

17:14.960 --> 17:17.250
on the day he killed
Gerald Reinhoff?

17:17.250 --> 17:21.380
No. No.
You mean even after spending
a year in solitary?

17:21.380 --> 17:23.420
The patient files
lead me to believe

17:23.420 --> 17:26.000
that Mr. Lahey
was only pretending

17:26.000 --> 17:29.460
to have delusions, uh,
and hallucinations,

17:29.460 --> 17:32.040
and this is a textbook sign
of malingering.

17:32.040 --> 17:33.880
Which means?

17:33.880 --> 17:36.040
Mr. Lahey is making up
his insanity

17:36.040 --> 17:38.250
to win a "not guilty"
verdict.

17:38.250 --> 17:40.620
Your witness.
Dr. Charmagne,

17:40.620 --> 17:44.000
why is your diagnosis
so different from Dr. Phillips,

17:44.000 --> 17:46.960
who declared my client insane
at the time of the murder?

17:46.960 --> 17:49.540
Our field of study is not
an exact science.

17:49.540 --> 17:50.830
So not because
your new boss

17:50.830 --> 17:53.000
told you to testify
against my client?

17:55.040 --> 17:58.250
Uh, excuse me?
Is it true that
Governor Birkhead hired you

17:58.250 --> 18:00.960
as the head of the new
mental health initiative?

18:00.960 --> 18:02.330
Objection.
Argumentative.

18:02.330 --> 18:04.540
I'm showing a connection
between the witness

18:04.540 --> 18:06.580
and Governor Birkhead,
who was the first defendant

18:06.580 --> 18:09.210
in the class action that
resulted in this trial.

18:09.210 --> 18:11.330
Overruled.
The witness will answer.

18:12.880 --> 18:15.790
Yes, I've been given a job
with the governor.

18:15.790 --> 18:19.540
Due to what is clearly a bribe
from the Governor's office,

18:19.540 --> 18:21.750
I move to strike
this witness' testimony...
Objection, Your Honor.
Speculation.

18:21.750 --> 18:22.920
...from the record!
Your Honor!

18:22.920 --> 18:25.330
I am in adamant agreement
with Ms. Keating.

18:25.330 --> 18:27.420
I instruct the jury
to disregard

18:27.420 --> 18:29.670
Dr. Charmagne's
entire testimony

18:29.670 --> 18:32.580
as it is biased
and lacking all credibility.

18:32.580 --> 18:34.750
[ Audience murmuring ]

18:34.750 --> 18:37.790
♪♪

18:37.790 --> 18:39.080
Great.
Great, yeah, yeah.

18:39.080 --> 18:41.620
Just set them aside.
I'll be there to pick them up.

18:41.620 --> 18:42.790
[ Cellphone beeps ]
What did Annalise assign you?

18:42.790 --> 18:45.290
A precedent list
and a pocket motion?

18:45.290 --> 18:48.460
Yeah, for an in limine hearing
we're never gonna have.

18:48.460 --> 18:50.210
[ Backpack unzips ]
Just so you know,
you will never be able

18:50.210 --> 18:52.460
to finish that
in one night.

18:52.460 --> 18:55.120
Well, thanks for the vote
of confidence.

18:55.120 --> 18:58.210
No, that's my way of
saying I'll help you.

18:58.210 --> 19:00.380
I'll come to your place
after I pick Christopher up --

19:00.380 --> 19:01.830
I mean, as long
as I can bring him.

19:02.920 --> 19:04.670
Yeah.

19:04.670 --> 19:06.380
But why would you
want to help me?

19:06.380 --> 19:07.880
Well, I'm gonna be
second chair pretty soon,

19:07.880 --> 19:09.830
and then I'll need
your help.

19:09.830 --> 19:14.540
♪♪

19:14.540 --> 19:15.880
Nate: Pops...

19:15.880 --> 19:19.580
if you want to talk your case,
Annalise should be here.

19:19.580 --> 19:21.580
You see, uh...

19:21.580 --> 19:23.210
This right here
is what I'm sick of.

19:23.210 --> 19:25.330
You telling me
how I should be,

19:25.330 --> 19:27.080
Annalise telling me
how I should be.

19:29.290 --> 19:30.880
You can be mad at me,
not her.

19:30.880 --> 19:32.000
I'm mad at both of you.

19:32.000 --> 19:33.460
We're losing this case.

19:33.460 --> 19:35.170
You don't know that.
I got eyes.

19:35.170 --> 19:37.460
I can see what that jury
is thinking.

19:40.330 --> 19:44.830
Nate, I want a chance
to talk to them myself.

19:44.830 --> 19:46.830
Trust Annalise.

19:46.830 --> 19:49.040
This is my life.

19:49.040 --> 19:51.040
And for just once,

19:51.040 --> 19:56.710
I want the chance to fight
for myself using my words,

19:56.710 --> 20:00.920
not having somebody else
call me crazy, or violent,

20:00.920 --> 20:02.540
or a liar.

20:02.540 --> 20:04.170
Me.

20:07.330 --> 20:09.620
I want my day
in court, man.

20:09.620 --> 20:13.540
♪♪

20:13.540 --> 20:15.250
Well, it's not me
you got to convince.

20:15.250 --> 20:17.580
Annalise sure as hell
ain't gonna listen to me.

20:17.580 --> 20:19.920
You think she'll
listen to me?
I've seen the way
she looks at you.

20:19.920 --> 20:22.750
Yeah, she'll listen to you
if you try hard enough.

20:25.790 --> 20:27.290
Please, son.

20:30.830 --> 20:35.580
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

20:37.040 --> 20:40.750
Hey.
Put together a list of every
major insanity defense

20:40.750 --> 20:43.040
in the last 50 years where
the defendant took the stand.

20:43.040 --> 20:44.250
Why?

20:44.250 --> 20:45.540
Why do you think?

20:45.540 --> 20:47.750
Our client's
taking the stand.

20:47.750 --> 20:48.750
That's crazy.

20:48.750 --> 20:50.210
Get on board.

20:52.540 --> 20:54.080
Thanks.

20:54.080 --> 20:55.580
Don't thank me yet.

20:55.580 --> 20:57.290
[ Cellphone thumps lightly ]

21:02.670 --> 21:04.500
That was kind of --
kind of aggro.

21:04.500 --> 21:05.750
In a good way?

21:05.750 --> 21:07.620
Well, more in a
"you made me feel like

21:07.620 --> 21:10.120
some random hook-up from Humpr"
kind of way.

21:10.120 --> 21:11.170
I'm sorry.

21:11.170 --> 21:12.540
I guess I just
got kind of lost

21:12.540 --> 21:14.380
in the moment
for a second.

21:14.380 --> 21:16.000
[ Breathes deeply ]

21:16.000 --> 21:17.620
Or you were thinking
of Annalise.

21:18.830 --> 21:21.710
Come on. You have every right
to be pissed at her.

21:21.710 --> 21:24.250
I mean, first, she boots you
off of the Supreme Court,

21:24.250 --> 21:26.380
and now she's booting you off
from the Senior case.

21:26.380 --> 21:27.830
Are you trying to
rile me up again?

21:27.830 --> 21:29.170
I want you to take
all the outrage

21:29.170 --> 21:31.000
that you've been
burying in sex

21:31.000 --> 21:32.500
and put it into
the class action.

21:32.500 --> 21:35.210
And for you to just quit
and let her scare you away,

21:35.210 --> 21:36.710
that's not like you.

21:36.710 --> 21:37.960
Well,
maybe it's the new me.

21:37.960 --> 21:39.500
Well, I don't want
to marry that guy.

21:39.500 --> 21:42.710
I want to marry the badass
social justice renegade.

21:42.710 --> 21:44.330
'Cause that's who
you really are.

21:46.330 --> 21:50.500
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

21:50.500 --> 21:51.830
Uh, it's my mom.

21:51.830 --> 21:53.290
Fingers crossed
the date works.

21:53.290 --> 21:55.170
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hi, Mom.

21:55.170 --> 21:58.120
Every high-profile insanity
defense from the '90s

21:58.120 --> 22:00.960
was won without putting
the defendant on the stand.

22:00.960 --> 22:02.420
Same thing in the '80s.

22:02.420 --> 22:04.330
Guess the only time
nutjobs testify

22:04.330 --> 22:05.500
is when they try to
defend themselves.

22:05.500 --> 22:08.250
[ Sighs ] Did you hear
Gabriel say "nutjob"?

22:08.250 --> 22:09.960
That's not a very nice
term to use

22:09.960 --> 22:12.120
when referring to
the mentally ill.

22:12.120 --> 22:14.040
Okay, please tell me you
do not talk to him

22:14.040 --> 22:15.500
like that all the time.

22:15.500 --> 22:17.620
Research shows that
when talking to your baby

22:17.620 --> 22:20.250
and making eye contact,
it helps brain development.

22:20.250 --> 22:22.880
That way my guy won't end up
being a serial killer, mnh-mnh.

22:22.880 --> 22:24.580
Why would he become
a serial killer?

22:24.580 --> 22:26.580
His dad pass down some
bad genes or something?

22:27.670 --> 22:29.750
♪ Don't you ever
leave me alone ♪

22:29.750 --> 22:31.250
His dad's not around.

22:31.250 --> 22:32.710
You know that.

22:32.710 --> 22:35.080
Yeah, I know, I just -- I know
you're a single parent.

22:35.080 --> 22:37.250
I just wasn't sure
if the father

22:37.250 --> 22:39.460
was completely
out of the picture.

22:39.460 --> 22:42.670
♪ My war is over ♪
Well, now you know.

22:42.670 --> 22:44.380
Your dad?

22:44.380 --> 22:46.120
Ghosted before I knew him.

22:46.120 --> 22:49.750
♪ Be my shelter from the storm ♪

22:49.750 --> 22:51.880
But we should, uh,
should get back to this.

22:51.880 --> 22:53.420
I'll take the '70s,
you take the '60s.

22:53.420 --> 22:56.040
Oh, the but the '70s
are so much juicier

22:56.040 --> 22:59.500
with the irresistible
impulse test ruling of 1971.
♪ My war is over ♪

22:59.500 --> 23:01.830
Fine, you can have
the disco years.

23:01.830 --> 23:03.670
[ Computer keys clack ]

23:03.670 --> 23:07.920
♪ I am a sad boy ♪

23:07.920 --> 23:12.330
♪♪

23:12.330 --> 23:18.380
♪ Don't you ever
leave me alone ♪

23:25.000 --> 23:31.000
♪ My war is over ♪

23:31.830 --> 23:33.620
♪♪

23:33.620 --> 23:37.710
♪ I am a sad boy ♪

23:37.710 --> 23:42.380
♪♪

23:42.380 --> 23:48.380
♪ Don't you ever
leave me alone ♪

23:52.210 --> 23:54.000
♪♪

23:54.000 --> 23:58.330
♪ My war is over ♪

23:58.330 --> 23:59.880
[ Sighs ]

24:00.880 --> 24:03.290
Annalise:
Mr. Lahey, how was solitary?

24:03.290 --> 24:04.790
Get much reading done?

24:04.790 --> 24:06.880
They don't let you do
no reading in there.

24:06.880 --> 24:10.790
W-W-Which is funny enough
because the lights are on 24/7.

24:10.790 --> 24:12.170
You know,
studies show that

24:12.170 --> 24:15.460
prisoners who fare the best
in solitary

24:15.460 --> 24:19.120
are the ones who have
a strategy to overcome it.

24:19.120 --> 24:21.040
What was yours?

24:21.040 --> 24:25.670
I had a photo of me and my son
that I snuck in.

24:25.670 --> 24:27.120
This photo here?

24:30.380 --> 24:31.790
Yeah, that's it.

24:31.790 --> 24:33.120
And it worked, too.

24:33.120 --> 24:34.580
It worked until
the guards took it,

24:34.580 --> 24:37.920
and then I went downhill
pretty fast after that,

24:37.920 --> 24:41.210
and after a few months,
all my thoughts just started

24:41.210 --> 24:43.750
smashing into one another,
and, uh,

24:43.750 --> 24:47.170
I started hearing things
and seeing things.

24:47.170 --> 24:49.040
And all that's because...

24:51.250 --> 24:53.880
...they took my son
away from me.

24:53.880 --> 24:56.960
So, after a year
in solitary,

24:56.960 --> 24:58.880
how'd you feel
when they let you out?

24:58.880 --> 25:01.380
I was...scared.

25:01.380 --> 25:03.880
I wasn't used to
people talking to me,

25:03.880 --> 25:05.460
you know, looking at me.

25:05.460 --> 25:07.380
So, how would you describe
the moment

25:07.380 --> 25:10.250
when your fellow inmate,
Mr. Reinhoff,

25:10.250 --> 25:12.960
a 280-pound
career criminal,

25:12.960 --> 25:15.420
approached you in the yard?

25:15.420 --> 25:18.040
Well, you know, he come at me,
talking smack.

25:18.040 --> 25:20.710
So, you know, I, uh...

25:20.710 --> 25:26.000
♪♪

25:26.000 --> 25:28.960
[ Breathing shakily ]

25:28.960 --> 25:30.750
I wasn't a man
at that moment.

25:30.750 --> 25:36.750
I was a -- I was a bomb
fixed to -- to explode,

25:38.880 --> 25:41.420
and I did, and I still
don't know why I did,

25:41.420 --> 25:43.920
but I did, and it doesn't
matter if it was him.

25:43.920 --> 25:46.330
It was gonna be somebody
because...

25:46.330 --> 25:51.580
♪♪

25:51.580 --> 25:53.040
[ Sighs ]

25:53.040 --> 25:57.120
That is what the SHU
did to me.

25:57.120 --> 26:02.670
It made me very sick
in my head.

26:02.670 --> 26:05.670
And so...

26:05.670 --> 26:08.040
[ Sighs ]

26:08.040 --> 26:09.920
I wasn't myself.

26:09.920 --> 26:19.670
♪♪

26:19.670 --> 26:22.920
♪♪

26:29.790 --> 26:31.170
[ Knocking on window ]

26:31.170 --> 26:33.420
[ Vehicle door opens ]

26:33.420 --> 26:34.710
[ Vehicle door closes ]

26:34.710 --> 26:37.670
[ Sighs ]

26:37.670 --> 26:39.420
I am so happy you called.

26:41.000 --> 26:44.040
I'm sorry it took so long.
You have to be honest.

26:44.040 --> 26:47.000
If that stupid HR form made you
freak out, just rip it up.

26:48.290 --> 26:50.210
I need to tell you
something.

26:56.960 --> 27:02.750
You asked me about my family
and why I don't talk to them.

27:02.750 --> 27:04.540
Mm-hmm.

27:09.670 --> 27:12.460
My father molested
me and my sister.

27:15.670 --> 27:20.580
It started when I was five,
she was six.

27:20.580 --> 27:22.290
My mother knew.

27:22.290 --> 27:24.000
It was how
they made money.

27:26.670 --> 27:30.920
Tapes, and...

27:30.920 --> 27:32.500
selling us to men.

27:39.330 --> 27:41.500
When I was 15,
I got pregnant.

27:44.960 --> 27:47.580
I had the baby, a boy.

27:49.880 --> 27:53.460
But my parents told me
he -- he died.

27:57.330 --> 27:59.000
And now...

28:02.290 --> 28:04.920
...I just found out
he might be alive.

28:04.920 --> 28:10.460
♪♪

28:10.460 --> 28:15.580
I'm sorry if this
is too much.

28:18.960 --> 28:20.620
No.

28:20.620 --> 28:23.500
I just don't know if now

28:23.500 --> 28:26.460
is the right time
for this for me.

28:26.460 --> 28:28.290
[ Sniffles ]

28:28.290 --> 28:30.120
Hey.

28:30.120 --> 28:32.000
Look at me.

28:32.000 --> 28:34.880
Bonnie.
[ Sighs ]

28:39.460 --> 28:41.250
You're the bravest person
I've ever met.

28:43.120 --> 28:45.080
I mean it.

28:45.080 --> 28:48.620
And I love you.

28:48.620 --> 28:50.830
No matter what,
I love you so much.

28:50.830 --> 28:57.670
♪♪

28:57.670 --> 29:04.210
♪♪

29:04.210 --> 29:06.580
[ Sighs ]

29:06.580 --> 29:11.580
♪♪

29:11.580 --> 29:14.080
[ Sobs, sighs ]

29:14.080 --> 29:16.580
♪♪

29:16.580 --> 29:20.420
Cox: Mr. Lahey, you said
that the altercation began

29:20.420 --> 29:24.120
when Gerald Reinhoff began
talking smack to you.

29:24.120 --> 29:25.500
Do you remember
what it was about?

29:25.500 --> 29:28.080
He said he -- he wanted
to fight the boxer.

29:28.080 --> 29:29.960
But on
your psych evaluation,

29:29.960 --> 29:32.920
you said that you were having
hallucinations at the time.

29:32.920 --> 29:34.880
Yeah, I was.

29:34.880 --> 29:36.000
Well, if that's the case,

29:36.000 --> 29:37.540
how is the jury
supposed to believe

29:37.540 --> 29:39.670
your made-up version
of events?

29:39.670 --> 29:42.960
Is it possible that
you threw the first punch?

29:42.960 --> 29:44.210
I didn't.

29:44.210 --> 29:45.540
Hm. Maybe
Joe Frazier did?

29:45.540 --> 29:47.210
He was your imaginary
cell mate, right?

29:47.210 --> 29:49.540
He's badgering
the witness --
The jury has a right to

29:49.540 --> 29:50.960
understand what
happened that day --
What happened that day

29:50.960 --> 29:52.380
is well-established --
I'm trying to tell you
what happened --

29:52.380 --> 29:53.710
Well,
why should we believe you?

29:53.710 --> 29:55.960
I know I have a lot of problems,
but I'm not stupid.

29:55.960 --> 29:58.500
I remember.
It was the worst day of my life.

29:59.710 --> 30:01.880
So, you knew?

30:01.880 --> 30:03.880
In the moment
you knew that

30:03.880 --> 30:05.420
that was the worst day
of your life?

30:05.420 --> 30:06.750
Well, that sounds like
you regret what you did.

30:06.750 --> 30:08.330
Your Honor, the counsel
is testifying --

30:08.330 --> 30:09.960
Agreed, cease this line
of questioning --

30:09.960 --> 30:12.620
But how could you feel regret
if you were insane at the time?

30:12.620 --> 30:13.960
Your Honor, stop this!

30:13.960 --> 30:15.620
Unless you're lying...
That's enough, Mr. Cox.

30:15.620 --> 30:17.380
[ Gavel bangs ]
...to push this sham
of a defense --

30:17.380 --> 30:18.540
I said that's enough!
[ Gavel banging ]

30:18.540 --> 30:20.580
I insist that you hold
Mr. Cox in contempt.

30:20.580 --> 30:22.880
He's intentionally confused
a mentally ill man

30:22.880 --> 30:25.080
to manipulate his testimony.
That's grounds for...

30:25.080 --> 30:26.830
So, what do we think?

30:26.830 --> 30:28.330
Do we count our
client's testimony

30:28.330 --> 30:30.830
for our side
or the prosecution's?

30:30.830 --> 30:32.080
The prosecution's.

30:32.080 --> 30:33.710
The jury left that testimony

30:33.710 --> 30:35.380
believing our client
knew the difference

30:35.380 --> 30:37.540
between right and wrong
when he killed Reinhoff.

30:37.540 --> 30:39.710
So you don't think I can
come back from that?

30:39.710 --> 30:41.170
I think you know
my answer by now.

30:42.620 --> 30:44.040
So, what do the rest
of you think?

30:44.040 --> 30:45.380
Because this moment right now

30:45.380 --> 30:48.380
is when the best lawyers
prove their worth.

30:48.380 --> 30:52.500
Closing arguments begin in...
three hours.

30:54.040 --> 30:56.210
So, let's discuss
how we can still win this case.

30:58.420 --> 30:59.880
Really?

30:59.880 --> 31:01.830
You've already
given up on me?

31:01.830 --> 31:05.710
No one in this room believes
that I can still win this?

31:08.460 --> 31:09.960
Professor Keating.

31:09.960 --> 31:12.120
Yes.

31:12.120 --> 31:14.080
I think you should move
for a mistrial.

31:17.000 --> 31:19.210
You think I should
throw in the towel?

31:19.210 --> 31:21.460
It's better than
a guilty verdict.

31:21.460 --> 31:22.670
Here.

31:26.540 --> 31:27.790
During
Nate Junior's cross,

31:27.790 --> 31:29.500
Cox referred to Senior
as a crack dealer,

31:29.500 --> 31:30.670
but his arrest records show

31:30.670 --> 31:32.330
he was only arrested
for marijuana.

31:32.330 --> 31:34.080
Lying about crimes
he didn't commit is misconduct

31:34.080 --> 31:35.460
and grounds for a mistrial.

31:35.460 --> 31:37.290
I've already showed my hand
to the State.

31:37.290 --> 31:39.170
I'd have to build
a whole new defense,

31:39.170 --> 31:42.080
and who knows if our client can
even survive another trial --

31:42.080 --> 31:44.960
But he is your face case.

31:44.960 --> 31:47.000
Losing this will hurt
all of your class action appeals

31:47.000 --> 31:48.210
going forward.

31:48.210 --> 31:54.420
♪♪

31:54.420 --> 31:55.710
Okay.

31:55.710 --> 31:57.790
So, let's take a vote.

31:57.790 --> 32:01.420
Who agrees with Mr. Maddox that
I should move for a mistrial?

32:01.420 --> 32:11.210
♪♪

32:11.210 --> 32:14.290
Cox: The defense lied to you.
They lied.

32:14.290 --> 32:17.750
Mr. Lahey was a violent man
before he went to jail.

32:17.750 --> 32:22.330
So I don't want you to fall
for the father-son sob story.

32:22.330 --> 32:25.380
Instead, I want you to think of
the victim who was murdered

32:25.380 --> 32:28.420
before he had the chance
to start his own family.

32:28.420 --> 32:32.080
I urge you to find
the defendant guilty

32:32.080 --> 32:34.420
of the murder
of Gerald Reinhoff.

32:34.420 --> 32:41.500
♪♪

32:41.500 --> 32:42.960
Ms. Keating?

32:42.960 --> 32:47.380
♪♪

32:51.920 --> 32:53.960
Ms. Keating?

32:53.960 --> 33:03.170
♪♪

33:03.170 --> 33:08.670
492,750.

33:08.670 --> 33:11.750
That's how many minutes
Nathaniel Lahey, my client,

33:11.750 --> 33:15.540
spent in a cement box
smaller than a parking space.

33:15.540 --> 33:19.830
Now, the prosecution claims that
Nathaniel's time in solitary

33:19.830 --> 33:21.620
did not make him insane,

33:21.620 --> 33:24.830
even though a neutral,
court-appointed doctor

33:24.830 --> 33:27.080
testified that it did.

33:27.080 --> 33:29.920
Not to mention numerous studies
that prove

33:29.920 --> 33:34.750
that solitary confinement causes
severe psychological disorders.

33:34.750 --> 33:37.500
The facts of the case are clear.

33:37.500 --> 33:40.670
Nathaniel Lahey
went into solitary confinement

33:40.670 --> 33:42.290
for less than a year,

33:42.290 --> 33:44.620
and just days after he got out,

33:44.620 --> 33:46.830
he did something
he'd never done before.

33:46.830 --> 33:48.500
He snapped.

33:48.500 --> 33:50.170
Exploded.

33:50.170 --> 33:52.620
He lost his mind.

33:52.620 --> 33:55.250
Now, if you still don't think
that that can happen,

33:55.250 --> 33:59.750
then I want you to put yourself
in his shoes for one minute,

33:59.750 --> 34:02.580
just a fraction of the time
that he spent there.

34:04.120 --> 34:05.670
Here.

34:05.670 --> 34:13.080
♪♪

34:13.080 --> 34:18.290
492,750 minutes,

34:18.290 --> 34:21.380
and all he heard was this.

34:41.460 --> 34:43.000
[ Breathes deeply ]

35:22.960 --> 35:24.830
[ Siren wails in distance ]
Connor.

35:24.830 --> 35:26.790
Hey.

35:26.790 --> 35:28.540
Just because I didn't go
for the mistrial

35:28.540 --> 35:30.620
doesn't mean it wasn't
a good idea.

35:30.620 --> 35:32.670
Okay.
Want me to tell Gabriel?

35:32.670 --> 35:33.920
Why?

35:33.920 --> 35:35.330
It was your idea.

35:37.250 --> 35:39.620
Maddox,
give this to Annalise.

35:39.620 --> 35:42.210
It's how she can get
a mistrial.
You can show her.

35:42.210 --> 35:44.420
She's gonna listen to you
over me right now.

35:44.420 --> 35:45.960
It's the only way
to win the case.

35:48.500 --> 35:50.080
You're the only one
who knew this case well enough

35:50.080 --> 35:51.920
to catch that detail.

35:51.920 --> 35:54.460
Yeah, well,
it doesn't matter.

35:54.460 --> 35:57.210
Your closing was great.
Hopefully the jury agreed.

35:57.210 --> 36:03.040
♪♪

36:03.040 --> 36:05.120
I shouldn't have taken you
off the case.

36:05.120 --> 36:07.830
♪♪

36:07.830 --> 36:09.250
[ Breathes sharply ]

36:09.250 --> 36:11.750
I'm trying to say
I'm sorry, Connor.

36:12.960 --> 36:14.670
[ Door opens ]
Gabriel: Professor Keating.

36:14.670 --> 36:17.960
The jury's back.

36:17.960 --> 36:20.500
My clerk's informed me the jury
has reached a verdict.

36:20.500 --> 36:23.540
Is this true?
We have, Your Honor.

36:23.540 --> 36:30.710
♪♪

36:30.710 --> 36:39.500
♪♪

36:39.500 --> 36:43.120
♪♪

36:43.120 --> 36:50.670
♪♪

36:50.670 --> 36:53.290
On the charge of
first-degree murder,

36:53.290 --> 36:56.380
the jury finds
Nathaniel Calvin Lahey...

36:56.380 --> 36:58.380
♪♪

36:58.380 --> 37:00.710
...not guilty
by reason of insanity.

37:00.710 --> 37:02.580
Yes!
Oh!

37:02.580 --> 37:03.670
Ohh.

37:03.670 --> 37:08.330
♪♪

37:08.330 --> 37:10.000
Judge Coughlin: At this time,
Mr. Lahey will be remanded

37:10.000 --> 37:11.710
back to the care
of the state

37:11.710 --> 37:13.920
until a suitable
psychiatric facility

37:13.920 --> 37:15.420
can be found for him.

37:15.420 --> 37:16.620
[ Gavel bangs ]

37:16.620 --> 37:18.960
[ Laughs ]

37:18.960 --> 37:20.920
You won.

37:20.920 --> 37:23.120
You told your story
and they listened.

37:23.120 --> 37:24.500
This was all you.

37:26.080 --> 37:27.750
Thank you.

37:27.750 --> 37:33.420
♪♪

37:33.420 --> 37:34.790
Reporter: How will today's
decision affect your appeals

37:34.790 --> 37:36.710
moving forward?

37:36.710 --> 37:39.580
I think winning is
a good strategy moving forward.

37:39.580 --> 37:40.960
Don't you?
[ Laughter ]

37:40.960 --> 37:42.460
This win is nothing.

37:42.460 --> 37:44.670
It's not even a drop
in the bucket.

37:44.670 --> 37:47.540
[ Camera shutters clicking ]
It's one step in
a 100-mile journey

37:47.540 --> 37:49.830
in wiping out injustices
in our legal system.

37:49.830 --> 37:51.880
So let's keep working

37:51.880 --> 37:54.330
to give the invisible population
in prisons

37:54.330 --> 37:56.000
the chance
to tell their stories

37:56.000 --> 37:58.920
in front of a jury.

37:58.920 --> 38:00.000
Wish
I could've done more.

38:00.000 --> 38:01.500
[ Chuckles ]

38:01.500 --> 38:03.290
No, all is forgiven.

38:03.290 --> 38:05.790
You say that now,
but in a few days,

38:05.790 --> 38:07.380
once the high's worn off?
No, are you kidding?

38:07.380 --> 38:10.330
H-How can I expect
12 strangers to forgive me

38:10.330 --> 38:11.880
and I can't forgive
my own son?

38:11.880 --> 38:13.120
Huh?

38:13.120 --> 38:20.620
♪♪

38:20.620 --> 38:25.880
♪♪

38:25.880 --> 38:26.960
Mm.

38:26.960 --> 38:28.580
♪♪

38:28.580 --> 38:31.960
And this win isn't just
for people behind bars.

38:31.960 --> 38:35.620
It's a win for all people
who feel like the system,

38:35.620 --> 38:39.000
our justice system,
is making them go crazy.

38:39.000 --> 38:40.920
You should be standing
behind her.

38:40.920 --> 38:43.880
But before we continue,
I want to take this moment...
So you can get in a photo,
send it to your mom.

38:43.880 --> 38:45.420
...to thank the students
in my clinic...
Not my style.

38:45.420 --> 38:48.830
...for their tireless support
and dedication on this case.

38:48.830 --> 38:51.460
I know they will bring the same
level of skill and commitment

38:51.460 --> 38:52.620
to our many other clients

38:52.620 --> 38:55.210
awaiting their own chance
for justice.

38:55.210 --> 38:57.920
I also want to thank...
You here to spy on me?

38:57.920 --> 38:59.830
Don't flatter yourself.
I got to talk to Annalise.

38:59.830 --> 39:01.620
About Gabriel?

39:03.000 --> 39:05.330
What about him?
As much as I wanted
to believe your story

39:05.330 --> 39:07.500
that you were looking into
all the new students --
That's true --

39:07.500 --> 39:09.420
All I had to do is find out
where he lives!

39:09.420 --> 39:10.790
Wes's building!

39:10.790 --> 39:12.210
And when I asked him
how he ended up there,

39:12.210 --> 39:13.920
that some guy he
"hoops with"

39:13.920 --> 39:15.000
told him about
the apartment.

39:15.000 --> 39:17.500
...populations in prison...

39:17.500 --> 39:18.830
Who the hell is he?

39:18.830 --> 39:20.620
...in front of a jury.

39:20.620 --> 39:22.580
Reporter #2:
Well, what does this mean
for the rest of your plaintiffs?

39:22.580 --> 39:24.960
Annalise: It means that the
Supreme Court agrees with us.

39:24.960 --> 39:26.540
The juries agree with us.

39:26.540 --> 39:28.670
The only people who
don't agree with us

39:28.670 --> 39:30.420
are the officials
who run this state.

39:30.420 --> 39:31.790
And I don't blame them --

39:31.790 --> 39:34.500
I mean, we're the ones
cleaning up their mess.

39:34.500 --> 39:36.120
Is that a shot
at Governor Birkhead?

39:36.120 --> 39:38.330
I respect Governor Birkhead.

39:38.330 --> 39:40.580
Listen, she has a tough job.

39:40.580 --> 39:43.170
She oversees billions
of dollars,

39:43.170 --> 39:45.040
thousands of employees,

39:45.040 --> 39:46.920
and I'm just one little
defense attorney

39:46.920 --> 39:49.080
that keeps beating her
in court.

39:49.080 --> 39:51.290
That can't be fun.

39:51.290 --> 39:52.380
Bring her in.

39:52.380 --> 39:53.620
Let's see if she's
got the balls

39:53.620 --> 39:55.420
to say any of this
to my face.

39:57.920 --> 39:59.540
-Senior!
-Solitary whaaaat?!

39:59.540 --> 40:01.080
-To Nate Senior!
-[ Laughs ]

40:02.540 --> 40:04.170
[ Whispering ] You think
now's a good time to tell them?

40:04.170 --> 40:06.750
[ Whispering ] Not yet.
Hmm, okay.

40:06.750 --> 40:09.380
Enough whispering, you two.

40:09.380 --> 40:10.710
You're having sex,
aren't you?

40:10.710 --> 40:13.670
Oh, God, no!
Gross-eries! [ Laughs ]

40:13.670 --> 40:15.670
Connor and I deserve to know
if our best men are boning.
Mm-hmm.

40:15.670 --> 40:19.250
[ Laughs ]
Uh, we're not boning.

40:19.250 --> 40:21.460
We're...

40:21.460 --> 40:23.500
planning your joint
bachelor party!

40:23.500 --> 40:25.210
Operation Slama Jama!

40:25.210 --> 40:27.250
-Pew! Pew! Pew! Pew! Pew!
-Pew! Pew! Pew! Pew! Pew!

40:27.250 --> 40:29.420
-No one told you to do that.
-I don't want one of those.

40:29.420 --> 40:31.080
Well, we're doing it,
and we're doing it here,

40:31.080 --> 40:32.580
because we're all poor.

40:32.580 --> 40:33.960
So, don't be surprised

40:33.960 --> 40:35.500
if the only stripper
we can afford is me.

40:35.500 --> 40:37.290
It's gonna be this Friday,
so mark your calendars.

40:37.290 --> 40:39.500
No, my mom is coming
on Friday.
[ Gasps ]

40:39.500 --> 40:41.210
Wait, what? We said no moms
until the wedding.

40:41.210 --> 40:42.750
I know, I know,
but the Senior case

40:42.750 --> 40:45.920
gave me all the parent feels,
and I invited your mom, too.

40:45.920 --> 40:47.830
I'm sorry.
Oliver!

40:47.830 --> 40:52.040
I'm sorry.
Oh, this is gonna be the best
bachelor party ever!

40:52.040 --> 40:53.790
-You know it!
-Hey!

40:53.790 --> 40:55.420
Asher: Oh, I got to order
more penis hats.

40:55.420 --> 40:57.710
[ Door opens ]
Where the hell are you?

40:57.710 --> 40:59.000
Frank said you weren't home.

40:59.000 --> 41:00.580
I'm fine. Don't worry.

41:00.580 --> 41:03.170
Just tell me where you are.

41:03.170 --> 41:05.620
Outside Julie's.

41:05.620 --> 41:07.670
Don't do anything.
I'll come right there.

41:07.670 --> 41:09.120
We can do this together.

41:09.120 --> 41:12.710
I'm not alone.
Ron drove me.
What?

41:12.710 --> 41:15.710
Bonnie, we don't even know
if he can handle this.

41:15.710 --> 41:19.040
I'll call you
as soon as I'm done.

41:19.040 --> 41:21.420
I promise.

41:21.420 --> 41:22.670
[ Cellphone beeps ]

41:22.670 --> 41:25.960
♪♪

41:25.960 --> 41:27.380
[ Knock on door ]

41:27.380 --> 41:31.040
♪♪

41:31.040 --> 41:33.210
[ Door creaking open ]

41:33.210 --> 41:39.080
♪♪

41:39.080 --> 41:40.040
Hey.

41:42.000 --> 41:43.880
[ Baby crying ]

41:43.880 --> 41:45.540
Connor:
Anyone seen my husband?

41:45.540 --> 41:49.710
♪♪

41:49.710 --> 41:52.540
Oli?

41:52.540 --> 41:53.830
Oliver.

41:53.830 --> 41:55.670
Where the hell are you?!

41:55.670 --> 41:57.210
Oliver!

41:57.210 --> 41:59.790
If you're out here,
I'm seriously gonna kill you!

42:02.000 --> 42:03.620
Oliver!

42:03.620 --> 42:08.080
♪♪

42:08.080 --> 42:09.420
Mom?

42:09.420 --> 42:15.080
♪♪

42:15.080 --> 42:17.080
♪♪

42:31.000 --> 42:33.000
♪♪

42:38.120 --> 42:44.120
♪♪

42:45.290 --> 42:51.290
♪♪
